race.comment: ULYSSES BLUE (11) returns and it's worth noting she filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last time in work over 1000m at this track. Strong chance to kick the campaign off on the right note. CAN'T TOUCH THIS (10) settled well back then made some inroads and finished fifth last time out over 1000m at Kembla Grange two weeks ago. Steps up in journey and holds winning claims. SURE INTENTIONS (13) will be hoping to pick straight back up from where he left off last campaign, scoring two on the bounce. Trial in readiness should have him raring to go under the light weight. VEREEVA (12) continues to leave herself with too much to do but could cause a scare late if they overdo it in front. Don't dismiss.
